main event: A civilian observed a round-oval shaped object in the eastern sky near Wilmington, Ohio on September 28, 1966.
interesting points: The object had an apparent ring around it that would disappear and reappear.
The object seemed to change its relative position to itself.
The observer could not see the object again after looking around to try to find a plausible explanation.
No previous reports of unusual sightings were found from the Clinton County APB or the ATC control tower and FAA.
The object was classified as 'Unidentified' in the report.
